            
    ### SSH Authorized Keys Module Info File ###

    This module takes SSH public RSA key and places it in authorized_keys file of choosen user.
    If no key is given, it is created and placed in /tmp directory with random name.
    If no user is given, one of available authorized_keys files is choosen from /home directory 
    or root user's authorized_key file is used.

    OPTIONS:
    
    USER        Required: NO    Username of choosen authorized_keys owner
    KEY_PATH    Required: NO    Path to own, earlier generated, key file (.pub)
